      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Ah, the \"Sleeping Gloom\" is just a fancy name for the router's internal Wi-Fi signal being so weak it looks like a ghost, but it's not actually a ghost! It's a goblin named \"Signal Sickness\" that has been eating your router's battery life and turning your internet into a slow-motion movie.\n\nSince you need to get back to work, let's skip the poetry and get to the **actual technical steps** to wake up this goblin.\n\n1.  **Hard Reset (The Goblin's Wake-Up Call):**\n    *   Find the small, round button on the back of your router (usually labeled \"Reset\").\n    *   Use a paperclip or a pin to press and hold it for **10 to 15 seconds**.\n    *   *Goblin Note:* This is the only way to force the router to forget its old passwords and forget the \"Sleeping Gloom.\"\n\n2.  **Power Cycle (The Goblin's Nap Cycle):**\n    *   Unplug the power cord from the wall outlet.\n    *   Wait **30 seconds**. (This is crucial; the goblin needs time to fully wake up and",
